The paper deals with constructing numeric invariants from the computation of a multidimensional persistence module, which is a topic in computational topology. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with constructing invariants, which is a topic in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of algebraic topology, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
